sources.title: Princess Charming
sources.description: “”Wonderful lighthearted spoof” “Fascinating curio of the West End and Broadway” “This film couldn’t finish fast enough” (IMDB reviews quotes). An operetta-like musical comedy with an outstanding cast and Evelyn Laye in the title role. The adaptation of a play by F Martos. IMDB rating 6.8. Directed by Maurice Elvey. UK release 1934. US release 1935. Complete print (see Special Note). A. K.A. “Alexandra” SPECIAL NOTE: This video file was originally encoded by whomever as a widescreen film, which it certainly is not. So if the cast members appear to be shorter and stouter than you would expect, it is what it is.
